  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-01",
    "date": "2021-05-24T14:40:38Z",
    "text": "Saudi Arabia Accountability for Gross Violations of Human Rights Act\n\nThis bill imposes visa-blocking sanctions on specified foreign persons determined to have played a role in the killing of Jamal Khashoggi, and it requires the Department of State to report on incidents of arbitrary detention, violence, and state-sanctioned harassment by Saudi Arabia against U.S. citizens and their family members. The bill also requires the State Department to make publicly available a report that describes whether and how a concurrence with Saudi Arabia for U.S. security assistance will avoid identifying the United States with governments that deny human rights and fundamental freedoms to their people."
  },
